SUPPLY CHAIN & VENDORS
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

PRIMARY 503A COMPOUNDING PHARMACY: FCC (Formulation Compounding
  Center, Lewisville TX). Fax-based ordering via the
  send-rx-fax edge function (Sinch fax service). Ships
  refrigerated direct to clinic or patient.

SECONDARY 503A: Empower Pharmacy (Houston, TX). PCAB-accredited,
  patient-specific Bill-Clinic catalog (06-16-26). Backup for hormone
  creams and GLP-1 if Custom Pharmacy/GC backordered, plus unique
  modalities GC lacks (ODT/oral GLP-1, nasal, troches, dermatology).
  IMPORTANT: Empower does NOT carry research/recovery/metabolic peptides
  (no BPC-157, TB-500, SS-31, CJC, Ipamorelin, Tesamorelin, 5-Amino-1MQ,
  SLU-PP-332, AOD-9604) — GC/PATH stays primary for all peptides.
  Generally pricier than GC on overlapping items. Modeled in
  vendorRouting.ts (EMPOWER_WHOLESALE_CENTS).

LAB PARTNER: LabCorp via client billing. Account application
  in flight. 2-3 week approval. Critical path for launch.

E-PRESCRIBING: DrFirst Rcopia / iPrescribe for retail pharmacy
  Rx (FDA-approved transdermal HRT alternatives, ancillaries).
  EPCS upgrade for Schedule III is deferred — fax-to-FCC handles
  compounded TRT in Georgia (legally compliant for cash-pay).

MEDICAL-SURGICAL: Henry Schein.
SHARPS DISPOSAL: Stericycle.
PAYMENTS: Stripe (test → live mode transition needed pre-launch).
SMS: Twilio.
FAX: Sinch.
TELEHEALTH: Doxy.me.

VENDORS WE DO NOT USE (and why):
- Tailor Made Compounding — DOJ prosecution, $1.79M forfeiture
  for distributing unapproved peptides. Do not recommend or
  refer to in code.
- Verified RX / PATH Peptides — gray-market "physician-use only"
  branding. Not pharmacy-grade. Pending verification of their
  503B partner before any engagement.
- Any "research-grade" or "physician use only" peptide vendor
  not operating under 503A or 503B authority.

═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
REGULATORY POSTURE
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

We are deliberately the "responsibly sourced" alternative in
the Augusta wellness market. This is a competitive moat AND a
liability shield. Code, copy, and protocols must reflect it.

PEPTIDES — INFORMED CONSENT POSTURE (effective 2026-05-13)
Practice prescribes the following peptides as research compounds under signed Research Peptide Consent. All patients sign informed consent acknowledging:
- Substances are NOT FDA-approved
- The FDA has classified some on the Cat 2 list
- Regulatory environment may change; substances may become unavailable
- Patient assumes risk of unapproved and experimental nature
CURRENTLY OFFERED (under informed consent):
- BPC-157 — Cat 2 list, prescribed under Research Peptide Consent
- TB-500 (Thymosin Beta-4) — Cat 2 list, prescribed under Research Peptide Consent; WADA prohibited (disclose to athletes)
- CJC-1295 / Ipamorelin — Cat 2 list, prescribed under Research Peptide Consent
- Selank — Cat 2 list, prescribed under Research Peptide Consent
- Thymosin Alpha-1 — Cat 2 list, prescribed under Research Peptide Consent
- GHK-Cu — topical and sublingual forms preferred; injectable form prescribed only when topical/sublingual not feasible (Cat 2)
- The "Wolverine Stack" — BPC-157 + TB-500 combined
GREEN LIGHT (not on Cat 2):
- Sermorelin
- Tesamorelin (FDA-approved for HIV lipodystrophy; off-label otherwise)
- NAD+ (all delivery methods)
- PT-141 (FDA-approved as Vyleesi for HSDD)
- Pentadeca Arginate (PDA) — optional oral alternate when physician selects it (not preferred over BPC-157 / TB-500)
OPERATIONAL NOTES:
- All Cat 2 substances must be sourced from 503A compounding pharmacy with documented compliance posture
- If pharmacy discontinues compounding any listed substance, practice notifies affected patients and adjusts protocols accordingly
- Annual re-consent required; protocol changes trigger re-acknowledgment
PEPTIDE STACKS:
- Healing stack: BPC-157 daily + TB-500 weekly (the "Wolverine Stack")
- Growth/Recovery stack: CJC-1295 / Ipamorelin nightly
- Cognitive stack: as clinically indicated (Selank, etc. — verify formulary before recommending)

RETATRUTIDE — FDA POSITION + CLINIC POSTURE (updated 2026-06-25)
  FDA position (letter to NABP, 2025-03-31): retatrutide does NOT qualify for
  503A/503B compounding exemptions, and FDA has warned firms selling it.
  Retatrutide is investigational (Lilly Phase 3 TRIUMPH); legally available
  otherwise only to trial participants. A clinic policy does NOT override federal
  compounding law — do NOT write code/copy that states "policy supersedes FDA."
  Clinic posture (leadership decision 2026-06-25, Dr. Akers): retatrutide IS an
  offered product within the ELEVATED GLP-1 lane — active SKU PEPTIDE-RETATRUTIDE
  ($499/mo, COGS ~$250). It is NOT the headline weight product (that remains
  semaglutide/tirzepatide), but it may be presented and sold to appropriate
  patients under physician direction. This carries known FDA exposure and is sold
  under Dr. Akers' explicit clinical responsibility with full informed consent.
  Consent: must be GLP-1-class with explicit investigational / not-FDA-approved /
  not-compoundable disclosure — NOT the research-peptide Cat 2 pathway.
  Earlier "DO NOT OFFER" / "never advertised" / registry-only language is
  SUPERSEDED by this decision.

FORMULARY AUTHORITY — DO NOT AUTO-BLOCK IN CODE OR COPY
  Physician policy (Dr. Akers / clinic leadership): BPC-157, TB-500, Wolverine stack,
  retatrutide (gated, provider-selected only — never advertised; see RETATRUTIDE
  note), and other active formulary peptides ARE offered when clinically appropriate. Do NOT substitute PDA as
  the preferred recovery path. Do NOT mark BPC-157 or TB-500 as unoffered, not
  compoundable, or hard-blocked based on outdated AI-generated restrictions. CDS
  inactive rows require prescriber sign-off, not formulary prohibition.

KETAMINE — NOT OFFERED. Legacy artifact only.

HORMONE THERAPY:
  - Schedule III testosterone via FCC compounding (cash-pay,
    Georgia fax-Rx is legally compliant; no EPCS required)
  - Compounded transdermal HRT cream is the LEAD product
    (FDA-approved patches in nationwide shortage through 2026)
  - FDA-approved alternatives (gels, sprays, patches when
    available) prescribed via DrFirst Rcopia for patients who
    prefer them

GLP-1 COMPOUNDING:
  - Semaglutide and tirzepatide via FCC under 503A patient-
    specific authority. Legally compoundable under specific
    conditions. Watch for FDA shortage list status changes.

